No specific URLs. That's why we have HTTPS.
The specific URL is encapsuled in the encrypted HTTPS packet.
What they could see is if the specific sites are on different servers - and thus IPs.
Like boards.4chan for the boards themselves and i.4cdn for the images.
Everything after the slash (behind the .org/) isn't visible, unless you look at the packet's encrypted content.
